<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}={78}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{4}{y}={43}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={78}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{78}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{\left(\frac{{{78}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+{4}{y}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left({78}\right)}--\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({9}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{78}-{\left(-{9}\right)}{y}+{4}{y}={43}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}={43}-{78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{y}+{\left({4}\right)}{y}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9}+{\left({4}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{y}=-{35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{35}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{\left({7}\right)}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({63}\right)}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={78}-{\left({63}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{15}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>